race.description: Apg Yearling Sales 2YO C&G Final Mobile Trot (G1)
race.comment: Progressive youngster NOTANOTHA NAUGHTY (12) made it three in a row when he pushed to the front and kept going to score at this circuit and distance last week. A wide draw on the back row is a challenge but he showed his toughness when he raced parked but dug deep for a fighting Redwood Classic win two back. HOWDY MATE (11) has also three put three wins together, all of them at this circuit and distance. This is a much trickier draw than he had in winning by close to 2m last week but that was his first hitout for seven weeks and it should have improved him. KEAYANG BAZLENKA (9) was beaten for the first time last week when he raced parked and finished just over a metre behind NOTANOTHA NAUGHTY. Peaking third-up and looks to be the one on the up. THE PREACHER (3) is consistent and draws better than many of his main rivals so expect to be competitive again.
